NVIDIA VIDEO CODEC SDK LICENSE

The files under this directory are derived from the NVIDIA Video Codec SDK
sample code (https://github.com/NVIDIA/video-sdk-samples).

Two distinct licenses apply:

1. MIT License — applies to SDK header files:
   - include/nvEncodeAPI.h
   - include/cuviddec.h
   - include/nvcuvid.h
   - include/Utils/Logger.h

   See the MIT license text in each file header.

2. NVIDIA Software Developer Kits, Samples and Tools License Agreement
   (with distribution rights) — applies to sample source code and utilities:
   - NvCodec/NvEncoder/NvEncoder.cpp
   - NvCodec/NvEncoder/NvEncoder.h
   - NvCodec/NvEncoder/NvEncoderCuda.cpp
   - NvCodec/NvEncoder/NvEncoderCuda.h
   - NvCodec/NvDecoder/NvDecoder.cpp
   - NvCodec/NvDecoder/NvDecoder.h
   - include/Utils/NvCodecUtils.h

   These files are provided under the NVIDIA end user license agreement (EULA)
   associated with the NVIDIA Video Codec SDK. The full license text is
   reproduced below.

   By using these files, you agree to be bound by the terms of this agreement.
   The license permits incorporation into products in binary form and
   redistribution of modifications to source code, provided recipients accept
   the same license terms.

   Full license text:
   https://github.com/NVIDIA/video-sdk-samples/blob/master/Samples/LicenseAgreement.pdf

